(
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFF9DC932FEC7FEE5FE72FE4A" box="[354,508,366,393]" captionStart="FIGURES 285–291" captionStartId="70.[151,264,1792,1816]" captionTargetBox="[165,1415,317,1757]" captionTargetId="figure-93@70.[155,1432,309,1769]" captionTargetPageId="70" captionText="FIGURES 285–291. Meri vanini spec. nov. 285–288 male (MPEG 30859, paratype), left palp (285 prolateral, 286 ventral, 287 retrolateral, 288 detail of embolus, ventral); 289–291 female (MZSP 37241, paratype) (289 epigyne, 290 vulva, 291 schematic course of internal duct system). C—conductor; E—embolus; EP—epigynal pocket; FD—fertilization duct; ft—first turn of duct system; GP—glandular projection; LL—lateral lobe; MS—median septum; PTA—prolateral tibial apophysis; RpP—retro proximal projection; RTA—retrolateral tibial projection; SdP—subdistal projection; SP—spermathecae; ST—subtegulum; tp—tegular protrusion. Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550516" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550516/files/figure.png" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Figs 285–288</figureCitation>
) by the palp with embolus with long, distad, laminar subdistal projection and barely conspicuous membranous region (see 
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFF9DC932FDF5FE19FD3DFE6E" box="[592,691,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURES 99–102" captionStartId="30.[151,264,1875,1899]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,669,1852]" captionTargetId="figure-289@30.[151,1436,669,1852]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURES 99–102. 99 Meri vanini spec. nov. 99, 101 IBSP 227036, male; 102 IBSP 5352, female; 100 Meri conduri spec. nov. MPEG 30809, male. 99 epiandrium, epiandrous spigots (arrows point to clusters of spigots); 100 right palp, embolus, detail of membranous region; 101 right palp, embolus, detail of membranous region; 102 left palp, sensory setae. mr—membranous region." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550269" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550269/files/figure.png" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Fig. 101</figureCitation>
). They are distinguished from both species by the RTA, distally tapering and bearing small triangular dorsal branch at base (
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFF9DC932FCEDFE3DFC24FE12" box="[840,938,439,465]" captionStart="FIGURES 238–244" captionStartId="59.[151,264,1821,1845]" captionTargetBox="[190,1385,470,1788]" captionTargetId="figure-83@59.[186,1401,453,1797]" captionTargetPageId="59" captionText="FIGURES 238–244. 238–241 Meri quinari spec. nov., male (UFMG 10165), left palp (238 prolateral, 239 ventral, 240 retrolateral, 241 detail of embolus); 242–244 Meri rivai spec. nov., female (IBSP 246428) (242 epigyne, 243 vulva, 244 schematic course of internal duct system). db—dorsal branch of RTA; E—embolus; EP—epigynal pocket; ft—first turn f duct system; FD—fertilization duct; GP—glandular projection; LL—lateral lobe; MAB—muscle attachment bands; MS—median septum; PTA—prolateral tibial apophysis; RTA—retrolateral tibial apophysis; SdP—subdistal projection; SP—spermathecae. Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550494" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550494/files/figure.png" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Fig. 240</figureCitation>
) (RTA distally blunt and without additional branches in 
<taxonomicName id="4C3E4D7AFF9DC932FEBBFE51FE1BFE36" authority="Rheims &amp; Jäger, 2022" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Jäger" authorityYear="2022" box="[286,405,475,501]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Meri" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tambor" status="spec. nov.">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFF9DC932FEBBFE51FE1BFE36" box="[286,405,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">M. tambor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFF9DC932FE39FE51FD80FE36" bold="true" box="[412,526,475,501]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2795790FF9DC932FE39FE51FD80FE36" box="[412,526,475,501]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" rank="species">spec. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C3E4D7AFF9DC932FDE1FE51FD3EFE37" authority="Rheims &amp; Jäger, 2022" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Jäger" authorityYear="2022" box="[580,688,475,500]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Meri" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vanini" status="spec. nov.">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFF9DC932FDE1FE51FD3EFE37" box="[580,688,475,500]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">M. vanini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFF9DC932FD12FE51FCA7FE36" bold="true" box="[695,809,475,501]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2795790FF9DC932FD12FE51FCA7FE36" box="[695,809,475,501]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" rank="species">spec. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
). Females are unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3246572FF9DC932FF62FE74FE10FCD6" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B8136F9FF9DC932FF62FE74FB55FD32" blockId="60.[151,1437,150,825]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFF9DC932FF62FE74FED7FDDB" bold="true" box="[199,345,510,536]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Description.</emphasis>
Male (
<typeStatus id="5485885BFF9DC932FE0DFE75FD9FFDD9" box="[424,529,511,538]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">holotype</typeStatus>
): Total length 11.4. Prosoma 5.3 long, 4.8 wide. Opisthosoma 6.0 long, 3.3 wide. Eyes: diameters: 0.45, 0.36, 0.30, 0.35; interdistances: 0.30, 0.10, 0.43, 0.50, 0.32, 0.20. Legs: I: 28.9 (8.6, 2.9, 8.3, 8.7, 2.1); III: 21.5 (6.4, 2.4, 5.7, 5.4, 1.6); IV: 24.0 (7.1, 2.2, 6.2, 6.6, 1.9). Spination follows the generic pattern except tibiae I–II: d1-0-1; tibiae III–IV: d0. Palp: PTA subtriangular, distally rounded, wider than long; RTA 1.7 times longer than wide (retrolateral view), irregularly conical; subtegulum visible between 8:30–10 o’clock in ventral view; tegulum slightly depressed close to conductor base; conductor widest at base, distally fanned; embolus subdistally curved with subdistal projection 1.5 times longer than wide (
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFF9DC932FC1AFD5DFBD3FD32" box="[959,1117,727,753]" captionStart="FIGURES 238–244" captionStartId="59.[151,264,1821,1845]" captionTargetBox="[190,1385,470,1788]" captionTargetId="figure-83@59.[186,1401,453,1797]" captionTargetPageId="59" captionText="FIGURES 238–244. 238–241 Meri quinari spec. nov., male (UFMG 10165), left palp (238 prolateral, 239 ventral, 240 retrolateral, 241 detail of embolus); 242–244 Meri rivai spec. nov., female (IBSP 246428) (242 epigyne, 243 vulva, 244 schematic course of internal duct system). db—dorsal branch of RTA; E—embolus; EP—epigynal pocket; ft—first turn f duct system; FD—fertilization duct; GP—glandular projection; LL—lateral lobe; MAB—muscle attachment bands; MS—median septum; PTA—prolateral tibial apophysis; RTA—retrolateral tibial apophysis; SdP—subdistal projection; SP—spermathecae. Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550494" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550494/files/figure.png" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Figs 238–241</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFF9DC932FBCDFD5CFB41FD32" box="[1128,1231,726,753]" captionStart="FIGURES 245–249" captionStartId="60.[151,264,1964,1988]" captionTargetBox="[157,1424,1113,1931]" captionTargetId="figure-352@60.[151,1435,1101,1941]" captionTargetPageId="60" captionText="FIGURES 245–249. 245–247 Meri quinari spec. nov., male (UFMG 10165, holotype), left palp (245 prolateral, 246 ventral, 247 retrolateral); 248–249 Meri rivai spec. nov., female (IBSP 246428, holotype) (248 epigyne, 249 vulva). Scale lines 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550496" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550496/files/figure.png" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">245–247</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8136F9FF9DC932FF62FD71FE10FCD6" blockId="60.[151,1437,150,825]" box="[199,414,763,789]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFF9DC932FF62FD71FEA6FCD6" bold="true" box="[199,296,763,789]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Female:</emphasis>
unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3246572FF9DC932FF62FC94FCE4FCFA" box="[199,874,798,825]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8B8136F9FF9DC932FF62FC94FCE4FCFA" blockId="60.[151,1437,150,825]" box="[199,874,798,825]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFF9DC932FF62FC94FEEFFCFB" bold="true" box="[199,353,798,824]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Distribution.</emphasis>
Only known from the 
<typeStatus id="5485885BFF9DC932FDC5FC95FD1EFCFA" box="[608,656,799,825]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">type</typeStatus>
locality (
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFF9DC932FD5EFC95FCD3FCFA" box="[763,861,799,825]" captionStart="FIGURES 319–320" captionStartId="77.[151,264,1914,1938]" captionTargetBox="[161,1427,181,1890]" captionTargetId="figure-17@77.[161,1427,181,1890]" captionTargetPageId="77" captionText="FIGURES 319–320. 319 distribution map for species of Meri gen. nov. (M. vanini spec. nov., M. munduruku spec. nov., M. aparia spec. nov., M. quinari spec. nov., M. rivai spec. nov.) 320 distribution map for all species of the genera Sadala Simon and Meri gen. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550428" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550428/files/figure.png" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Fig. 319</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
